{"questionId":"22154473","questionHtml":"<p>The following diagram shows a semicircle with centre <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math> and diameter <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>PQ</mi></math>. A rectangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OABC</mi></math> is also shown, such that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OA</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/62719333010bebf535001b65d7ba73cd41208da6.png\" width=\"685\" height=\"254\"></p>\n<p>Find the length of the arc <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BQ</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>(recognition that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OB</mi></math> is a radius)</p>\n<p>(radius<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo></math>)&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>89</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER (finding angle BOQ)</strong></p>\n<p>correct calculation for finding <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>arctan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp; </strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>expressing <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math>&nbsp;as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>90</mn><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>90</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>arctan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp; </strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>arctan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>147</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>994</mn><mo>º</mo></msup><mo>…</mo></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp; </strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>58299</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p>substituting <em>their</em> radius and angle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math>&nbsp;correctly into arc length formula&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>arc</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>BQ</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>90</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>arctan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mrow><mn>360</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><msqrt><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfenced></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>arctan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mfenced><msqrt><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfenced></math></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>24</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>24</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3679</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR (finding angle BOP)</strong></p>\n<p>correct calculation for finding angle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>arctan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>substituting <em>their</em> radius and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math>&nbsp;correctly into arc length formula&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em> (M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>arc</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>BP</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>arctan</mi><mo> </mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfenced><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mstyle></mrow><mn>360</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><msqrt><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>subtracting <em>their</em> arc <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BP</mi></math> from arc <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>PQ</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>arc</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>BQ</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msqrt><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>arctan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mrow><mn>360</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mfenced><msqrt><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>24</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>24</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3679</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22154473","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ1.11","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"The following diagram shows a semicircle with centre O and diameter PQ. A rectangle OABC is also shown, such that AB=8 and OA=5. Find the length of the arc BQ.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"11","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.3—Angles of elevation and depression","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.4—The circle, arc and area of sector, degrees only"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}